missions since they're not directly needed to understand the examples themselves.\n\nLooking at the s4 section, the use case explaining when to use this pattern—specifically handling visual feedback during processing delays—isn't captured in the knowledge file, which is worth noting as a minor gap since it helps clarify the pattern's purpose.\n\nFor the code examples, the missing `displayMethod=\"NORMAL\"` attribute and the absent `SqlRow` and `SqlResultSet` hints are all minor issues—they don't block implementation but represent incomplete documentation. Given that the v4 hints check is already marked as minor severity, I'm confident there are no critical findings here. I'll mark this as \"has_issues\" with all minor-level omissions.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18464,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18464,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a59b513-68fd-4d4f-a776-7fe788d86ba3","uuid":"8edf4dfd-62a6-4265-8f6b-e45472ade794"}
